This paper is about improving non-autoregressive neural machine translation models, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes two methods that involve generating phrase tables and transforming word embeddings, which are related to machine learning techniques such as adversarial learning and neural networks. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses the WMT14 and WMT16 datasets, which involve image captioning and machine translation tasks, respectively. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
